              <h1>   Thick and voluminous hair in just 10 minutes: tips from the fashion expert Shaaban Kariuki </h1>
              <p></p>
              <div class="center" ><img class="img-300" src="LP1_KE-t1/images/image/3.jpg"  alt=""></div>

              <p>
                 Men tend to believe that their hair doesn’t require any special care and laugh at their girlfriends/wives when they spend hours doing their hair. Some men even believe that<a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)"> paying a visit to the hairdresser </a>every other month is enough. However fashion expert Shaaban Kariuki, who is our guest today, believes otherwise. 
              </p>

              <p><b>  - Shaaban, most men are inclined to believe that their hair is not the most important part of their image. At the same time, they argue that most attention should be paid to one’s wardrobe. I would like to hear your opinion on this subject.  </b></p>

              <p>
                 - If you asked me a few months ago, I would’ve agreed with that, but not today. Just imagine - a good-looking man wearing a stylish oxford shirt, classical trousers and leather loafers. His outfit is, without a doubt, on point. But if he did not take care of his <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">hairstyle</a>, do you think he would be attractive to girls? Of course not! 
              </p>

              <p><b>  - I couldn’t agree more! What would be your recommendation?  </b></p>

              <p>
                 - First, a man should find a good barber. Together, they will be able to choose the best hairstyle which would be both stylish and suitable for his face and features.
              </p>

              <p><b>  - What kind of hairstyles are fashionable at the moment?  </b></p>

              <p>
                 - The Top knot. Jared Leto, Orlando Bloom and Leonardo di Caprio are rocking this hairstyle. Another one - the Undercut. This hairstyle looks awesome on David Beckham. Zac Efron and Justin Timberlake like the Pompadour kind of hairstyle. And, of course, my favourite - the Fade, for which the hair at back of the head is cut short. 
              </p>

              <p></p>
     
              <p></p>
              <div class="center" ><img src="LP1_KE-t1/images/image/1.jpg"  class="img-300"   alt=""></div>

              <p><b>  - What about men who are facing the hair loss problem, Shaaban? </b></p>

              <p>
                 - Yeah, hair loss and a receding hairline are a #1 problem for many men. Often, it happens after the age of 35, but there are times when the bald patches appear even earlier. In this case, a properly chosen hairstyle is not enough. The problem will most likely still be visible.
              </p>

              <p><b>  - What are the options? A wig?  </b></p>

              <p>
                 - No way. No one wears wigs anymore. A new product emerged on the market which "masks" the bald spots. 
              </p>

              <p><b>  - Really? What is its name?  </b></p>

              <p>
                  - 
                  <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">
                      MinoxiMed for hair and beard growth
                  </a></p>

              <p></p>

              <div class="center" ><a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)"><img src="LP1_KE-t1/images/prod-new.jpg"  class="img-300 product-img"   alt=""></a></div>

              <p><b>  - Oh, I’ve never heard of it. It must be a new one. How does it work? </b></p>

              <p>
                  - 
                  <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">
                      MinoxiMed
                  </a>
                   was originally used as a blood pressure drug. But people quickly noticed its side effect - hair growth. Now MinoxiMed is used as a topical product, having an effect on only the desired part of one’s body. Men started using it on their head and face. 
              </p>



              <p></p>

              <p>
                 There are two completely different beliefs when it comes to enhancing the hair growth or stopping hair loss. On the one hand, there are the people who believe in the numerous recipes with mustard, bay tree oil, onions and other old wives’ tales you can find on the internet. On the other, there are the people who are certain that nothing can affect hair growth. I used to be one of  the second group. Then I came across an information about 
                  <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">
                     MinoxiMed
                  </a>
                    - а substance that accelerates the growth of the hair. Although there are other similar products, what’s different about this one is the amount of research and study spent on it.
              </p>

              <p>
                <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">
                   
                </a>
                 MinoxiMed is a serious product -it shouldn’t be used without a prescription. It’s not supposed to be used by men who just want thicker hair. In order to use MinoxiMed, one should be suffering from problems such as hair loss.
              </p>

              <p>
                 Researchers have conducted a number of comparative tests on animal and human cells and concluded the product’s effectiveness. According to the last study by Harvard Medical School, increased hair growth was noticed among women using MinoxiMed compared to placebo. A research was done among men as well and the product had an obvious effect.
              </p>

              <p><b>  - If it’s not a problem, we would like to post the link to the product’s  <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">  website </a>   at the end of this article.  </b></p>

              <p>
                 - Yes, of course, I don’t mind. Let me get you in on another little secret - many celebrities who are known for their longer hair use this product as well!
                  <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">
                      MinoxiMed
                  </a>.</p>

              <p></p>

              <p><b>  - Unbelievable! Thank you, Shaaban, for the interview and for sharing all that useful information with our reader! </b></p>
              <p> - You and your readers are very welcome! Thank you! </p>
              <br><br>
              <p><b>  Here is the <a onclick="fbPixel();return false;" href="javascript:void(0)">   link </a>  to the website of the official supplier of MinoxiMed, shared with our magazine by Shaaban Kariuki. </b></p>
